A ride you will thank us for.Aside from safety, probably the most important benefit a hitch can provide is a great ride. When our engineers were designing the Companion, a major emphasis was on providing the smoothest ride available. If you've ever pulled a 5th Wheel trailer with another hitch, you know how stopping and starting can nearly give you whiplash! That's because traditional latching systems don't match the kingpin tightly. Our hitch was engineered with locking jaws that perfectly fit the king-pin meaning that there are no sloppy starts and stops. In addition, the coupler of the Companion sits on arms that are coated with polyurethane bushings, this means that where other hitches give you metal on metal contact, the Companion gives you a cushioned, quiet ride. Finally, instead of just front-to-back cushion, the Companion features a built-in shock absorber that allows gentle side-to-side movement without the slamming. This is a ride you deserve to experience!

title: For Sale:  AK-47 SAR-1 WITH ACCESSORIES, AND EXTRA MAGAZINES
postcontent:
This is for an SAR-1 AK-47, butt stock cleaning kit, sling, and 5 steel 30 round magazines. The furniture is all original Romanian military, solid front, laminate rear, this is completely un-messed with.

The SAR series was banned from importation in 2003, so they are rare, and hard to find now, further I had a smith re-add the bayonet lug, thread the barrel, and install correct pattern slant break, plunger, and spring, all Romanian military parts were used.

The SAR is unique as being the only correct patterned stamped Receiver AK to feature BOTH Y dimples, which makes it the most correct AK clone on the market, and also makes it ideal as a host for an NFA (full auto) conversion if you have your SOT License. It also features a factory optics rail.

This is NOT to be confused with the garbage WASR's, this is a completely different model, and unlike the WASR's is actually good.

I have pictures, but I'm having some technical issues so I will have to text them to you if you want to see them.

Note: The manufacturer is Cugir, but that was not in the drop down menu, so I selected the importer instead.

The Kobra site is NOT included, but is available for an extra $450.

The Kobra sight also has not been imported in a number of years, and is even harder to find than the rifle, it also is the type which uses common AA batteries.

title: For Sale:  Ruger LC9 with Crimson Trace Guard plus extras and 9mm ammo
location: Northern / downtown, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Ruger LC9 with Crimson Trace Guard package & ammo

Please note that the gun looks much better in person than what my cell phone is taking today.

The Package Includes:
the Ruger LC9 itself (obviously)
Crimson Trace Laser Guard
1 – Metal Belt Carry Clip
2 - 7 Round Magazines with Pinky Extensions
1 – 7 Round Flush Magazine (for really deep concealment)
3 – New Batteries (1 new in the guard and 2 extra ones I'll give you)
1 – Soft Pocket Holster
1 – Custom Built Kydex Pocket Holster
1 – “Discrete” Multiple Position Magazine Holster
Enhanced Raised Texture Grip on the Gun and on Pinky Extensions
Original Box, Carry Pouch, Lock and Paperwork
500 – 115 grain FMJ's (your choice of Winchester or Federal)
  50 – 115 grain JHP's (I use Federal JHP's for self defense with all of my guns)

Some of it's features:
100% Reliable Handgun – it's a Ruger (I've put 600 rounds though it – every single one was flawless; you can easily expect it to last 100,000 more rounds in it's lifetime. This is an extremely accurate gun – if you're not hitting the bullseye with this, don't blame the gun - LOL)
100% Reliable Laser – it's a Crimson Trace (you can sight it in for whatever distance you want, I have it at 15 feet because I figure that's where I'd need it very fast if I ever needed it)
It's a very good looking gun (I know that matters to some people).
It was designed for smaller hands yet works great with huge hands as well (check out Hickock45 on Youtube).
An extremely smooth and crisp trigger (I had a gunsmith detail clean the gun and then polish all the friction parts, which only cost $40; I was so happy with the results that I brought in 4 more handguns after that to get them done, too!)
Wonderful 3 dot iron sights (I'm not usually a big fan of 3 dot sights, but these are actually really good)
Small and thin enough to carry & FULLY conceal in many different ways (ankle, appendix, small of back, shoulder, every pocket I've tried (even back pants pockets), it'll even hold inside a cowboy boot!) 
Softened and rounded edges/corners for comfortable carry all day every day and to make sure you don't snag anything if quickly pulling it out of a pocket or your waist.
Several safeties built in that keep you safe, yet they don't get in the way if you ever need the gun fast or under pressure. You can keep the safeties off all the time if you like, which is what I did.
Rear site is adjustable for windage but it's been dead on since day one so I haven't touched it.
Although it's perhaps the lightest 9mm that many would say is reliable enough to trust your life to, it has very little recoil because of it's lower design making the second and third shots VERY fast (especially when using the laser!).
Like I said, it's incredibly light. You can easily wear it with sweatpants or shorts by using one of the holsters and the side clip, knowing it's safe and secure while being completely hidden and ready to use in a moments notice if ever needed. 
No special buttons to press to put the laser on or off; when you grip the gun ready to fire the laser comes on, when you let go some of the pressure it turns off – no wasted batteries by it turning on accidentally and then not working when you need it in a life saving situation.
Extremely intuitive and user friendly handgun. I hate to say that you won't need to practice shooting because I feel everyone should consistently practice shooting whatever they carry, but if you miss a trip or two to the range you won't have to feel guilty. It point shoots like a dream (or nightmare I suppose if you're on the other end of the barrel), the sights are great and quick to align and then you of course have the Crimson Trace Handguard which makes a beginner shooter decent and an experienced shooter a marksman.
The only reason I'm selling this is because lately I've been carrying a revolver and I think I'm going to stick with the revolver for a while.

Total for everything would cost just under $985 new; but even though it looks new, it isn't (the ammo IS factory fresh new) - but I figure it's got to be worth at least $800 … but I'm only asking $750 with the 500 rounds of FMJ and 50 rounds of JHP ammo or $650 without the ammo because I've always gotten good deals myself and been luck enough to have dealt with good, honest people when buying on Armslist, so I like to pass the good deals on the few times I'm selling something here, too.
Cash is always king, but I am open to all sorts of trades (not carry handguns though, I'm sticking with my .357 for now). Money can be added on either end as far as I'm concerned.
